SERVICE AGREEMENT

Last updated 29 March 2013.

The following terms and conditions apply all website development, maintenance and hosting services provided by IDDQD Limited to <%= company_name %> ("Client").

This Internet-based online service (“Service”) is provided by IDDQD Limited and is subject to the terms and conditions of this customer agreement ("Agreement"). This Agreement constitutes the entire agreement between the Client and IDDQD Limited. By using the Service, the Client confirms its acceptance of, and agreement to be bound by, this Agreement.

1. Acceptance and Effective Date

If the Client accepts a Service then the Client will be deemed to have satisfied itself as to the terms and conditions and have accepted this Service Agreement in full.

This Agreement takes effect on the date on which the Client signs this Agreement and continues until the Service relationship is terminated either by the Client or by IDDQD Limited. 

All pages on the Website are subject to review, modification and deletion without notice by IDDQD Limited. IDDQD Limited reserves the right in its sole discretion to change its policies at any time.

The Client is responsible for reviewing regularly information posted online to obtain timely notice of such changes. The Client's non-termination or continued use of the Service after changes are posted constitutes its acceptance of this agreement as modified by the posted changes.

2. Services Provided

__________________________________________________________

The Client may opt into either of the following Services:

a. Takeaway Starter

i. Under the "Takeaway Starter" Service, IDDQD Limited will provide to the Client:

- design, setup and maintenance of an instance of IDDQD Limited's proprietary takeaway e-commerce platform ("IDEAL Takeaway") through which the Client can advertise, accept and execute orders for its takeaway business; and

- phone support for reasonable trouble-shooting maintenance queries during the hours of 09:00-17:00 Mondays - Fridays, with reasonable efforts made at all other times.

ii. Client may upgrade from the "Takeaway Starter" Service to the "Takeaway Partner" Service at any time upon agreement with IDDQD Limited.

iii. Where the Client upgrades its service in accordance with Clause 2.a.ii., the Service Agreement will still operate.

............................................................

b. Takeaway Partner

Under the "Takeaway Partner" Service, IDDQD Limited will provide to the Client:

- design, setup and maintenance of an instance of IDDQD Limited's proprietary takeaway e-commerce platform ("IDEAL Takeaway") through which the Client can advertise, accept and execute orders for its takeaway business;

- phone support for reasonable trouble-shooting maintenance queries during the hours of 09:00-17:00 Mondays - Fridays, with reasonable efforts made at all other times;

- online and offline marketing services (including SEO or online ad spend); and

- discounts on optional devices for the Client's back office operations and delivery.

__________________________________________________________

3. Client Review and Content Control

a. IDDQD Limited will provide the Client with an opportunity to provide input to the design and content of the website during the design phase. 

b. Not withstanding Clause 3.a), final decisions as to the design and content of the Website will be made by IDDQD Limited.

4. Website Content

a. During the course of the engagement, the Client is to make reasonable efforts to:

i. provide website content which may include text and images; and

ii. provide photographic images.

b. IDDQD Limited may assist with photography as may be agreed with the Client.

c. IDDQD Limited does not endorse or stand behind the accuracy, truthfulness or reliability of any information (including statements of opinion or advice) provided on or by means of the Service. 

d. IDDQD Limited is not, under any circumstances, responsible for any copyright or royalty payments arising from content displayed by means of the service. 

5. Intellectual Property

a. The Client retains the copyright to data, files and graphic logos provided by the Client, and grants IDDQD Limited the rights to publish and use such material for the duration of this Service Agreement.

b. The Client must obtain permission and rights to use any information or files that are copyrighted by a third party. The Client is further responsible for granting IDDQD Limited permission and rights for use of the same and agrees to indemnify and hold harmless IDDQD Limited from any and all claims resulting from the Client's negligence or inability to obtain proper copyright permissions.

c. This Service Agreement shall be regarded as a guarantee by the Client to IDDQD Limited that all such permissions and authorities have been obtained.

d. IDDQD Limited reserves the right to re-use any customisable template design at a later stage if appropriate.

e. The structure, layout, design and any webpage content (words and pictures) supplied by IDDQD Limited remains the intellectual property of IDDQD Limited and must not, under any circumstances, be used without IDDQD Limited's explicit consent . The IDDQD Limited will defend all attempts to copy, reproduce or plagiarise its intellectual property.

6. Fees, Charges and Commission

Takeaway Starter

a. Unless agreed otherwise with the Client, the following applies to fees, charges and commission payable by the Client to IDDQD Limited.

i. Daily charges accrue from the date upon which the Website is uploaded to the server ("Launch Date"), at a rate of one pound per day (£1), invoicable on the first friday of each month.

ii. Commission also accrues from the Launch Date, at a rate of 10% of the total sum of each successfully completed transaction ("Website Revenue"), invoicable on the first Friday of each month.

b. In the event that the Commission and Daily Fee collectively exceeds Website Revenue, the following will apply.

i. Payment for services is due to IDDQD Limited by bank transfer. Bank details will be made available on invoices.

ii. IDDQD Limited will send the Client invoices via email. Invoices are due upon receipt. 

iii. Accounts that remain unpaid thirty (30) days after the date of the invoice will be assessed a service charge in the amount of the higher of one and one-half percent (1.5%) or £30 per month of the total amount due.

c. In the event that Website Revenue exceeds Commission, IDDQD Limited will electronically transfer the net sum to the Client on the first Friday of each month.

d. IDDQD Limited reserves the right to revise its fees, charges and commission at the end of each quarterly financial period.

Takeaway Partner

a. Unless otherwise agreed with the Client, the following applies to fees, charges and commission payable by the Client to IDDQD Limited.

i. An annual subscription fee is payable from the date upon which this Service Agreement is signed.

ii. Commission also accrues from the Launch Date, at a rate of 7.5% of Website Revenue, invoicable on the first Friday of each month.

b. In the event that the Commission exceeds Website Revenue, the following will apply.

i. Payment for services is due to IDDQD Limited by bank transfer. Bank details will be made available on invoices.

ii. IDDQD Limited will send the Client invoices via email. Invoices are due upon receipt. 

iii. Accounts that remain unpaid thirty (30) days after the date of the invoice will be assessed a service charge in the amount of the higher of one and one-half percent (1.5%) or £30 per month of the total amount due.

c. In the event that Website Revenue exceeds Commission, IDDQD Limited will electronically transfer the net sum to the Client on the first Friday of each month.

d. IDDQD Limited reserves the right to revise its fees, charges and commission at the end of each quarterly financial period.

9. Default

a. Accounts unpaid 30 days after the date of invoice will be considered in default. 

b. In the event that the Client is in default, IDDQD Limited may, at its discretion:

i. terminate this Service Agreement without notice; and/or

ii. remove the Website from the server.

c. IDDQD Limited is not responsible for any loss of data incurred due to the removal of the Service. 

d. Removal of such material does not relieve the Client of the obligation to pay any outstanding charges. 

e. Clients with accounts in default agree to pay IDDQD Limited reasonable expenses incurred by IDDQD Limited in enforcing these Terms and Conditions.

10. Termination

a. Where the Client terminates this Service Agreement, notice of termination of services of 10 working days must be provided in writing. E-mail or telephone requests for termination of services will not be honoured until and unless confirmed in writing. No refunds for daily fees or commission will be issued under any circumstances. 

b. Where IDDQD Limited terminates this Service Agreement under a "Takeaway Partner" Service, IDDQD Limited will provide 10 working days notice and refund the subscription fee on a pro rata basis.

c. If upon the date of termination Commission or Website Revenue is outstanding, any payable sums are to be settled by either party within 10 working days of notice.

11. Liability

IDDQD Limited hereby excludes itself, its Employees and or Agents from all and any liability from:

Loss or damage caused by any inaccuracy;
Loss or damage caused by omission;
Loss or damage caused by delay or error, whether the result of negligence or other cause in the production of the web site;
Loss or damage to clients' artwork/photos, supplied for the site. Immaterial whether the loss or damage results from negligence or otherwise.

The entire liability of IDDQD Limited to the Client in respect of any claim whatsoever or breach of this Agreement, whether or not arising out of negligence, shall be limited to the charges paid for the Services under this Agreement in respect of which the breach has arisen.

12. Indemnity

All IDDQD Limited services may be used for lawful purposes only. The Client agrees to indemnify and hold IDDQD Limited harmless from any claims resulting from the Client or its customers use of the Service that damages the Client or any other party.

13. Service Maintenance and Usage

a. IDDQD Limited agrees to:

i. maintain all equipment required for its access to and use of the Service;
ii. maintain the reasonable security of its Customer identification, password and other confidential information; and
iii. cover charges for bandwidth and/or SSL.

b. IDDQD Limited makes no guarantee as to the availability of service and is not liable in anyway for loss of service. The IDDQD Limited reserves the right to delete any page it deems unacceptable for any reason without prior verbal or written notice.

14. Service Operations

IDDQD Limited reserves complete and sole discretion with respect to the operation of the Service.

15. Marketing

a. The Client permits IDDQD Limited to use the Website to engage in its own online marketing (including Facebook, Twitter, Search Engines) and offline marketing (including pamphlets).

b. The Client agrees that the Website may be presented in IDDQD Limited's portfolio during and after the course of the Service Agreement.

16. Upholding Orders

The Client is to make reasonable efforts to ensure that customer orders made on the Website are fulfilled.

17. Domain Names

a. IDDQD will own the domain name for the Website.

b. Client will agree to redirect any of its existing domain/s to the Website address. Payment and renewal of any such domain names is under the control of IDDQD Limited.

18. Severability

In the event any one or more of the provisions of this Agreement shall be held to be invalid, illegal or unenforceable, the remaining provisions of this Agreement shall be unimpaired and the Agreement shall not be void for this reason alone. Such invalid, illegal or unenforceable provision shall be replaced by a mutually acceptable valid, legal and enforceable provision, which comes closest to the intention of the parties underlying the invalid,

